Mommy's much better at it.

509
00:34:17,962 --> 00:34:20,849
- Are you looking for a chick?
- I am.

510
00:34:23,557 --> 00:34:26,438
Miss Farrell told us about that
when we went to the farm.

511
00:34:28,859 --> 00:34:31,628
But she says that those eggs can never
become a chicken,

512
00:34:31,753 --> 00:34:33,752
even though they come
out of a chicken.

513
00:34:34,963 --> 00:34:37,574
- Why's that?
- Because they're from the store.

514
00:34:39,339 --> 00:34:40,902
And you know what else?

515
00:34:41,027 --> 00:34:43,255
If you hold an egg up
and it has veins in it,

516
00:34:43,380 --> 00:34:45,416
you can shake it then eat it.

517
00:34:45,691 --> 00:34:46,541
Really?

518
00:34:47,366 --> 00:34:48,913
It's called addling.

519
00:34:54,193 --> 00:34:56,719
Is the baby gonna live
in grandpa Gene's room?

520
00:35:02,242 --> 00:35:05,728
It's not grandpa Gene's room.
It's the baby's room.

521
00:35:11,029 --> 00:35:13,068
I thought it was gonna be a girl.

522
00:35:13,526 --> 00:35:15,654
Well, I thought
you were gonna be a boy.

523
00:35:19,403 --> 00:35:21,410
Not all surprises are bad.

524
00:35:29,284 --> 00:35:32,674
- Everything's gonna be fine.
- That's what miss Farrell said.

525
00:35:33,717 --> 00:35:36,017
Well, then I guess it must be true.

526
00:36:00,088 --> 00:36:02,561
Burt Peterson's firing
was undignified.

527
00:36:03,262 --> 00:36:05,496
Building security...
That's all I'll say.

528
00:36:06,372 --> 00:36:08,266
Confirm a couple of rumors.

529
00:36:08,391 --> 00:36:10,514
Did he throw a desk chair
against a window

530
00:36:10,639 --> 00:36:12,544
only to have it bounce back
and knock him over?

531
00:36:13,211 --> 00:36:14,387
Not that I know of.

532
00:36:14,512 --> 00:36:16,955
Did he make a #2 in a file cabinet?

533
00:36:18,401 --> 00:36:20,385
Burt Peterson lived hard
and loved hard.

534
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:24,515
Harry here is an expert in media.

535
00:36:24,640 --> 00:36:26,642
Television...
The air, not the sets.

536
00:36:28,228 --> 00:36:30,270
Now Admiral television
sales are flat...

537
00:36:30,438 --> 00:36:31,387
We know that.

538
00:36:31,512 --> 00:36:33,094
But as we studied your indices

539
00:36:33,219 --> 00:36:35,451
we realized that
they're not flat everywhere.

540
00:36:35,576 --> 00:36:36,433
In fact,

541
00:36:37,032 --> 00:36:39,530
among negroes sales are
actually growing.

542
00:36:40,078 --> 00:36:42,741
- We know that too.
- You do?

543
00:36:46,553 --> 00:36:48,396
No, of course you do.

544
00:36:49,739 --> 00:36:52,710
These are your numbers,
but I think we've discovered

545
00:36:52,835 --> 00:36:54,361
an interesting strategy.

546
00:36:55,926 --> 00:36:57,506
This is "Ebony."

547
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:01,837
By negroes for negroes.

548
00:37:02,678 --> 00:37:03,678
"Jet."

549
00:37:04,926 --> 00:37:07,489
Space in these magazines
costs far less than

550
00:37:07,614 --> 00:37:09,364
what you currently spend...

551
00:37:10,865 --> 00:37:14,690
Daily newspapers that go just to
this market for pennies on the dollar.

552
00:37:15,491 --> 00:37:16,491
And?

553
00:37:23,439 --> 00:37:27,041
Shift a portion of the media budget
from lower-indexing white areas

554
00:37:27,166 --> 00:37:29,060
to this market where
it can do more good.

555
00:37:29,185 --> 00:37:32,165
They already like it, we can make them
buy more by increasing the exposure.

556
00:37:32,538 --> 00:37:34,740
A 5% sales bump in Detroit alone

557
00:37:34,865 --> 00:37:37,588
would make you the same profit as
a 2% increase systemwide.

558
00:37:38,738 --> 00:37:41,569
And ads on television geared
to this market and white markets

559
00:37:41,694 --> 00:37:43,176
will have double the effect.

560
00:37:43,490 --> 00:37:45,304
A negro ad and a white ad?

561
00:37:46,179 --> 00:37:49,600
So, Campbell, you're making twice
the ads for us now.

562
00:37:50,054 --> 00:37:51,968
No, do them together.

563
00:37:52,473 --> 00:37:53,437
Integrate it.

564
00:37:53,739 --> 00:37:55,302
I don't think that's legal.

565
00:37:56,301 --> 00:37:57,900
Of course it's legal.

566
00:37:58,240 --> 00:38:00,527
Look, this conversation is
not worth having.

567
00:38:01,937 --> 00:38:05,180
Who's to say that negroes aren't buying
Admiral televisions

568
00:38:05,305 --> 00:38:07,618
because they think
white people want them?

569
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,490
<i>Miss Olson is here to see you.</i>

570
00:38:17,117 --> 00:38:18,217
Send her in.

571
00:38:21,553 --> 00:38:22,674
Oh, sorry.

572
00:38:26,456 --> 00:38:29,255
I know he doesn't need clothes,
but don't return it.

573
00:38:29,856 --> 00:38:32,521
I'm the youngest.
I never had anything new.

574
00:38:32,988 --> 00:38:35,187
- You didn't have to do that.
- I did.

575
00:38:35,516 --> 00:38:38,716
No one told me they were all going
in on it together.

576
00:38:41,698 --> 00:38:44,863
I heard you were back at work,
but now I wonder if that's true.

577
00:38:45,134 --> 00:38:46,365
I invited you in.

578
00:38:48,362 --> 00:38:50,215
I don't know if this
is the best time.

579
00:38:51,202 --> 00:38:53,121
I don't know. It's kind of serious.

580
00:39:01,366 --> 00:39:03,996
I've been thinking
about my situation here

581
00:39:04,492 --> 00:39:07,177
and I'm so grateful to you
for all you've done.

582
00:39:08,746 --> 00:39:09,679
I just...

583
00:39:11,678 --> 00:39:12,878
Well, you know

584
00:39:13,459 --> 00:39:15,103
I'm paid very little.

585
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:17,833
My secretary doesn't respect me

586
00:39:17,958 --> 00:39:20,190
because I make $71 more a week
than she does.

587
00:39:20,592 --> 00:39:22,651
Maybe we need to get you
a cheaper secretary.

588
00:39:24,257 --> 00:39:26,837
Paul Kinsey does
the same work that I do,

589
00:39:26,962 --> 00:39:28,822
and not as well sometimes.

590
00:39:29,458 --> 00:39:31,368
And I don't know
if you read it in the paper,

591
00:39:31,493 --> 00:39:34,458
but they passed a law where women who
do the same work as men

592
00:39:34,583 --> 00:39:36,533
will get paid the same thing.

593
00:39:36,867 --> 00:39:37,867
Equal pay.

594
00:39:40,117 --> 00:39:41,461
It's not a good time.

595
00:39:41,629 --> 00:39:43,711
It's not a good time for me, Don.

596
00:39:44,068 --> 00:39:46,717
- Do you know how expensive the city is?
- It's not gonna happen,

597
00:39:47,055 --> 00:39:48,531
Peggy, not now.

598
00:39:48,656 --> 00:39:50,971
I'm fighting
for paperclips around here.

599
00:40:02,534 --> 00:40:03,534
Third time.

600
00:40:04,909 --> 00:40:06,236
It must be old hat.

601
00:40:21,229 --> 00:40:24,722
- You're gonna be fine, Peggy.
- I look at you and I think

602
00:40:26,978 --> 00:40:28,904
"I want what he has."

603
00:40:29,572 --> 00:40:30,510
- Really?

604
00:40:33,162 --> 00:40:34,612
You have everything,

605
00:40:37,224 --> 00:40:38,839
and so much of it.

606
00:40:43,151 --> 00:40:45,251
I suppose that's probably true.

607
00:40:55,900 --> 00:40:57,800
What do you want me to say?

608
00:41:02,467 --> 00:41:04,920
I don't think I could have been
any clearer.

609
00:41:06,948 --> 00:41:09,341
You see what's been going on here
the last six months?

610
00:41:22,658 --> 00:41:24,443
What if this is my time?

611
00:41:49,386 --> 00:41:51,423
- Where are you going?
- To the ladies' room.

612
00:41:51,548 --> 00:41:53,111
You want to join me?

613
00:41:53,973 --> 00:41:56,598
- Did you tell Don about duck?
- That's none of your business.

614
00:41:56,723 --> 00:41:59,659
Sure. They hear you're
shopping around, they'll want you more.

615
00:41:59,784 --> 00:42:01,601
But me, I'm sharing
my job with Kenny.

616
00:42:01,769 --> 00:42:03,177
I'm already redundant.

617
00:42:03,302 --> 00:42:05,536
You have relationships
with your clients. That's leverage.

618
00:42:05,661 --> 00:42:08,275
- Did you say something?
- It's my decision, Pete.

619
00:42:32,258 --> 00:42:36,149
If it isn't Martin Luther King.
I should drop kick you off the roof.

620
00:42:37,201 --> 00:42:40,084
Admiral television has
no interest in becoming

621
00:42:40,209 --> 00:42:42,434
a colored television company.

622
00:42:42,703 --> 00:42:43,853
But they are.

623
00:42:44,265 --> 00:42:47,204
It seems illogical to me
that they would reject an opportunity

624
00:42:47,329 --> 00:42:48,779
to make more money.

625
00:42:50,155 --> 00:42:53,330
- Then again, I'm in advertising.
- This is a sensitive issue.

626
00:42:53,455 --> 00:42:56,765
- Businesses hate that.
- Let me put it in account terms.

627
00:42:56,890 --> 00:42:59,703
Are you aware of the number of hand jobs
I'm gonna have to give?

628
00:42:59,828 --> 00:43:01,453
Am I being taken off the account?

629
00:43:01,621 --> 00:43:03,663
I'm going to have to pretend
I had you killed!

630
00:43:03,831 --> 00:43:05,707
Sales are flat.
I had to do something.

631
00:43:05,875 --> 00:43:07,986
I don't know if anyone's ever told you
that half the time

632
00:43:08,111 --> 00:43:10,493
this business comes down
to "I don't like that guy."

633
00:43:13,339 --> 00:43:15,174
Are we done with the flogging?

634
00:43:17,516 --> 00:43:19,991
It's never as good
as you think it's gonna be.

635
00:43:21,453 --> 00:43:23,767
If I may. Burt, Roger,

636
00:43:24,819 --> 00:43:28,355
it does seem as though there's money
to be made in the negro market.

637
00:43:29,143 --> 00:43:30,981
Obviously not with Admiral,

638
00:43:31,405 --> 00:43:34,110
but I don't think it would be wrong
of us to pursue it

639
00:43:34,328 --> 00:43:35,428
in some way.

640
00:43:35,954 --> 00:43:36,954
Really?

641
00:43:37,913 --> 00:43:39,407
I've just moved here.

642
00:43:40,276 --> 00:43:42,806
I'm a stranger in a strange land,

643
00:43:43,455 --> 00:43:47,082
but I can tell you that there's
definitely something going on.

644
00:43:48,830 --> 00:43:50,280
We'll look into it.

645
00:43:51,393 --> 00:43:52,587
You can go.

646
00:44:44,220 --> 00:44:46,079
- We're here!
- She's here!

647
00:44:47,918 --> 00:44:49,556
Welcome welcome.

648
00:44:51,268 --> 00:44:53,257
- Mommy!
- Careful.

649
00:44:53,382 --> 00:44:55,266
Here, let me take him.

650
00:44:59,968 --> 00:45:01,893
I missed you so much.

651
00:45:03,329 --> 00:45:05,294
Wait till you see your fridge.

652
00:45:06,267 --> 00:45:07,955
If there's a power outage,

653
00:45:08,309 --> 00:45:10,623
you can feed the entire street
for a month.

654
00:45:13,019 --> 00:45:15,580
Hi, baby. I'm your brother Bobby.

655
00:45:15,833 --> 00:45:18,043
Remember: you have to be careful.

656
00:45:18,331 --> 00:45:19,481
How was it?

657
00:45:20,392 --> 00:45:21,392
You know.

658
00:45:23,032 --> 00:45:24,232
Was all a fog.

659
00:45:25,587 --> 00:45:28,099
You're making a mistake
not forcing carla to stay.

660
00:45:29,265 --> 00:45:31,269
She's been away from her family,

661
00:45:31,641 --> 00:45:34,439
- and I can manage.
- I know some girls.

662
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:37,984
- You want something to eat?
- Sure.

663
00:45:38,152 --> 00:45:39,985
I've got it. Come on.

